SQL

when selecting from a table you can do SELECT(table.*) to grab everything from that table.
Query inside of query
* UPDATE addresses SET city = “New York”, state = “NY”, zip = 10108 WHERE user_id IN (SELECT id FROM users WHERE first_name = “Mitch”)

Active record
* its a ruby gem
* Object Relational Mapping - handles database connection for you
* takes a sql database and turns them into ruby objects that you may interact with then puts it back into the db
